    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-09-16T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-09-16T11:00:00-05:00" n="792"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d792">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00116 E.W./9–1644: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Algiers</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lawton</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="34" xml:id="d792fn34">Edward P. Lawton had been relieved of
                        his duties as secretary to the Mission at Algiers on September 13, the
                        Mission having moved on to Paris.</note>
                    <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Algiers</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-16T18:00:00+02:00"
                            >September 16, 1944—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 11:58 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>67. Note dated September 5 sent to Massigli incorporated Department’s 2554 [<hi
                        rend="italic">2555</hi>] September 2, 8 p.m. Acknowledgment received today
                    from Foreign Affairs Commissariat concludes with final paragraph summarized as
                    follows: “Provisional Government” being established in Paris, Commissariat can
                    only reserve comment on whether issuance of new declaration would not be useful
                    in present circumstance. Idea of following and intensifying propaganda already
                    made of subject responds exactly to suggestion expressed by French authorities.
                    Commissariat would be grateful to have competent services requested to renew and
                    develop as frequently as possible in its German language broadcasts warnings
                    already given regarding atrocities committed against civilians, prisoners and
                    internees.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lawton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
